      <p>When the documented steps don&rsquo;t hold, the cause is usually past the surface &mdash; a security program that re-blocks QuickBooks after each reboot, a proxy or corporate network policy intercepting the connection, SSL/TLS or system internet settings that won&rsquo;t hold, or a deeper installation or Windows-configuration issue. A Certified ProAdvisor with active Desktop and Enterprise certifications diagnoses the actual root cause, fixes it against a written scope, and verifies the update completes cleanly before closing &mdash; especially important when a payroll update is blocked near a deadline. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support.</p>
